e Contentful, Sanity, Strapi), or a simple backend.\n\n**Option 4: Website Builders / No-Code Platforms**\n\n*   Examples: **Webflow, Carrd (for single pages), Framer, Readymag.**\n*   **Benefits:** Visual design interface, no coding (or less coding) required.\n*   **Drawbacks:** Less flexibility, can be subscription-based. Webflow is very powerful and can achieve this look well.\n\n---\n\n**Design Principles to Emulate:**\n\n1.  **Typography:** Choose 1-2 clean, readable fonts (e.g., Inter, Montserrat, Open Sans, Lato). Use good font hierarchy (different sizes/weights for headings, body text).\n2.  **Color Palette:** Stick to a limited, cohesive color palette. Often a primary accent color, a secondary color, and neutrals (black, white, grays).\n3.  **Whitespace (Negative Space):** Don\u0027t cram elements together. Generous spacing improves readability and visual appeal.\n4.  **High-Quality Visuals:** Use clear screenshots, well-made GIFs, or even short demo videos.\n5.  **Consistency:** Keep the styling consistent across all pages and project details.\n6.  **Mobile-First/Responsive Design:** Ensure it looks good and functions well on all devices. Use CSS media queries.\n\n---\n\n**Steps to Get Started:**\n\n1.  **Plan Your Content:**\n    *   List all the projects you want to showcase.\n    *   For each project, gather:\n        *   Title\n        *   Tagline\n        *   Detailed description\n        *   List of technologies\n        *   Key features\n        *   High-quality visuals (screenshots, GIFs, hero image)\n        *   Links (live site, GitHub repo)\n    *   Write your \"About Me\" content.\n    *   Decide on your contact information.\n\n2.  **Choose Your Technology Stack:**\n    *   If you\u0027re comfortable with code: Start with HTML/CSS, or explore an SSG like Next.js or Eleventy.\n    *   If you prefer no-code: Look into Webflow or Framer.\n\n3.  **Design \u0026 Wireframe (Optional but helpful):**\n    *   Sketch out the layout for your homepage and project detail page. This helps visualize the structure before coding.\n\n4.  **Develop:**\n    *   **Homepage:** Create the grid/list of projects.\n    *   **Project Page Template:** Build the structure for a single project page.\n    *   **Styling:** Apply CSS to match the desired aesthetic. Focus on responsiveness.\n    *   **Populate Content:** Add your project data. If using an SSG, this might involve creating Markdown files for each project.\n\n5.  **Test:**\n    *   Test on different browsers and devices.\n    *   Check all links.\n\n6.  **Deploy:**\n    *   **Static Sites (HTML/CSS, SSGs):** Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages are excellent free/low-cost options.\n    *   **More Complex Apps:** Vercel (great for Next.js), Netlify, or other cloud hosting providers.\n\n---\n\nIf you tell me which technology you\u0027re most comfortable with or interested in learning, I can give you more specific guidance or code snippets for that approach!",
